A '''Kelly hose''' (also known as a ''mud hose'' or ''rotary hose'') is a flexible, steel reinforced, high pressure [[hose (tubing)|hose]] that connects the [[rig standpipe|standpipe]] to the [[Kelly drive|kelly]] (or more specifically to the goose-neck on the swivel above the [[Kelly drive|kelly]]) and allows free vertical movement of the [[Kelly drive|kelly]] while facilitating the flow of [[drilling fluid]] through the system and down the [[drill string]].<ref>http://www.clearcreekassociates.com/wordarchive/kellyhose.htm</ref> The '''Kelly hose''' has a diameter of 3-5 inches (inside diameter).<ref>http://www.glossary.oilfield.slb.com/Terms/k/kelly_hose.aspx</ref>

