{{Orphan|date=December 2013}}

'''Nohra Padilla''' is a Colombian environmentalist. She grew up in [[Bogotá]]. She has assumed a leading position in the Association of Recyclers of Bogotá, and of the National Association of Recyclers in Colombia, which organizes about 12,000 members. She was awarded the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] in 2013 for her contribution to waste management and recycling in Colombia.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goldmanprize.org/recipient/nohra-padilla |title=Prize Recipient, 2013 South and Central America. Nohra Padilla |publisher=[[Goldman Environmental Prize]]|accessdate=7 December 2013}}</ref>

