{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
'''Plymax''' is a building material, used in [[airplane]]s. It consists of a thin sheet of [[duralumin]] bonded to a thicker sheet of [[plywood]]. Most notably it was used in the [[Morane-Saulnier M.S.406]], and [[France|French]] aircraft of the 1930s. It was also used on the bodies of some cars such as a 1931 Triumph Super 9. The articulated body of the Trojan Tasker also used this material.

